  "prompt": "What is the difference between blazer, suit, and tuxedo?",
  "response": "Here are the key differences between blazers, suits, and tuxedos:\n\nBlazer:\n- Standalone jacket\n- Less formal than a suit\n- Usually made of solid color fabric\n- Can be worn with different colored pants\n- More versatile and casual\n- Often worn in semi-casual settings\n\nSuit:\n- Jacket and matching pants made from the same fabric\n- More formal than a blazer\n- Typically worn in business or professional settings\n- Can be worn in various colors and styles\n- Appropriate for work, meetings, and some social events\n\nTuxedo:\n- Most formal option\n- Typically black or midnight blue\n- Satin or silk lapels\n- Worn with specific accessories like bow tie, cummerbund\n- Typically worn at very formal events like weddings, galas\n- Usually worn in the evening\n- Requires specific dress shirt and shoes\n\nMain distinctions:\n- Formality: Tuxedo > Suit > Blazer\n- Matching fabric: Tuxedo and suit match, blazer does not\n- Occasions: Tuxedo (formal events), Suit (professional), Blazer (casual/semi-formal)",
